            <span class="text-content-offset text-sm ml-auto hidden sm:block">Prioritize critical stability fixes</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-4 py-3 last:pb-0">
            <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded bg-content text-page-base font-bold text-sm">3</span>
            <span class="text-content font-semibold">Evolution</span>
            <span class="text-content-offset text-sm ml-auto hidden sm:block">Sustainable long-term architecture</span>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<h2 id="gemini-5" class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 mt-16 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-content-offset">gemini-5</h2>
<section class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 md:py-16 lg:py-20" aria-labelledby="gemini-5">
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 lg:gap-12 items-center">
    <div class="hidden lg:block lg:order-2"></div>
    <div class="order-2 lg:order-1 space-y-6 flex flex-col justify-center">
      <div class="p-6 bg-content text-page-base rounded-2xl shadow-xl transform rotate-1 hover:rotate-0 transition-transform duration-300">
        <p class="text-lg font-medium leading-relaxed">
          You don't need a massive ops team. You need <strong>better platform abstraction</strong>. I build the systems that let your developers deploy safely, independently, and frequently.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

